{"questionId":"33602096","questionHtml":"<p>Find the coefficient of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>6</mn></msup></math> in the expansion of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>9</mn></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to form a product of binomial coefficient, a power of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></math> and a power of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></math> seen<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>9</mn></mmultiscripts><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>6</mn><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>9</mn></mmultiscripts><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>84</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong><strong>(A1)</strong> </em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>6</mn><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>9</mn></mmultiscripts></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>9</mn></mmultiscripts></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>84</mn></math>,&nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use the general term<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mi>r</mi><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>9</mn></mmultiscripts><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>r</mi></msup></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>672000</mn></math> (exact)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>A0</strong></em> for a final answer of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>672000</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>6</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33602096","referenceCode":"24N.2.SL.TZ2.2","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the coefficient of x6 in the expansion of 2x-59.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"2","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.9—Binomial theorem where n is an integer"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}